#02. HangulHanja


"Korean(iBus): 18.04 LTS (Bionic Beaver) Daily Build

1. Settings > Region & Language > Manage Installed Languages > [
Install ] > ibus-hangul...

2. Restart or Log out

3. Region & Language > Input Sources > "+" > Korean(Hangul) > "Add"
English (US) > "-"

4. Korean(Hangul) > Setup > iBusHangul Setup
 > Hangul toggle key...
   Hangul
   Shift+space
 > Hanja...
   Hangul_Hanja
   F9


"Korean(iBus): 17.10

1. Software Center > GNOME Tweaks > [ Install ]

2. GNOME Tweaks > Keyboard & Mouse > [ Additional Layout Options ]...
Korean Hangul/Hanja keys...
[v] Hardware Hangul/Hanja Keys

3. Settings > Region & Language > Manage Installed Languages > [
Install ] > ibus-hangul...

4. Restart or Log out

5. Region & Language > Input Sources > "+" > Korean(Hangul) > "Add"
English (US) > "-"

6. Korean(Hangul) > Setup > iBusHangul Setup
 > Hangul toggle key...
   Hangul
   Shift+space
 > Hanja...
   Hangul_Hanja
   F9


"Korean(fcitx): 17.01

1. $ sudo apt install fcitx fcitx-hangul
2. [System Settings...] - [Language Support] - "Install" - Keyboard input method system: fcitx
3. [System Settings...] - Text Entry - '+' - Hangul(fcitx) - Add


"Korean(fcitx): 16.04

"Install
1. $ sudo apt-get install fcitx-hangul
2. [System Settings...] - [Language Support] - "Install" - Keyboard input method system: fcitx
3. Restart

"Setting
1. [System Settings...] - [Keyboard] - Shortcuts - Typing
- Switch to next source: Disabled
- Switch to previous source: Disabled
- Compose Key: Disable
- Alternative Characters Key: Disabled

- Compose Key: Right Alt
- Switch to next source: Multikey
2. Top Menu... - fcitx - Configure Current Input Method
- Input Method - '+' - hangul
- Global Config - Hotkey
-- Trigger Input Method: Shift+Space, Shift+Space
-- Extra key for trigger input method: Disabled
- Global Config - Program
-- Share State Among Window: All
3. Logout

4. $ vi .config/fcitx/config
ShowInputWindowAfterTriggering=False
5. Top Menu... - fcitx - Restart   or   $ fcitx -r
